Events & Delegates:-

Events: An event is a special kind of delegate used to provide notification

usage: used in scenarios where one object needs to notify about a change(like a button clicks).

Syntax: public event EventHandler MyEvent;

Deligates: Type safe function pointer. A deligate is a type that represents reference to methods with a specific signature.

Syntax: 
    public delegates coid MyDelegate(string message);

Usages: Delegates allows methods to be passed as parameters
-----------------------------------------------

Ex: code


public delegate void GreetDelegate(string message);
public static void Greet(string message)
{ 
Console.WriteLine(message);
}
static void Main()
{
GreetDelegate greet = new Greet Delegate(Greet);
greet("Hello World");
}.
